The paper deals with the connection between communication complexity and optimization theory, specifically in the context of extended formulations and nonnegative factorizations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of theoretical computer science (cs.CC, cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM), as well as information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) due to the use of randomized protocols.
